          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Fragment kinetic energy distribution in the fission of",
                "Np-237 by reactor neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "3INDTRM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " APSARA reactor"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Swimming pool reactor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Neutrons in the irradiation position used were under-",
                "moderated and the neutron flux of energy above 1 MeV",
                "was estimated as about 10.**11 n/cm2/sec.",
                "Irradiation period varied from a few hours to 24 hours."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Np-237 obtained from ORNL was purified from Am,Pu and U",
                "The content of Pu-239 was less than 0.004%.",
                "By electrodeposition, 100 to 180 micro-gram of Np was",
                "deposited over an area of 1.5 cm2  and it was covered",
                "first with a stack of 1.9 mg/cm2 pure Al foil and was",
                "wrapped in 63 mg/cm2 pure Al, and finally was covered",
                "with about 200 mg/cm2 cadmium foil to reduce the",
                "formation of Np-238."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC",
                "RCHEM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Radiochemical and gamma-ray",
                "spectroscopic method. The thin-target integral range",
                "measurement technique was employed to measure the",
                "recoil ranges of fission products."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ge(Li) detector for direct counting of the",
                "catcher foils on the detector.  Detail, see S.P.Dange",
                "et al.,2nd Int.Conf.on Phys.and Chem.of Fission,Vienna",
                "1969,p.741."
              ]
            }
          ],
