              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Total primary kinetic energy of fission fragment."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The recoil ranges of fission products were converted",
                "into kinetic energies using two different range-energy",
                "equations.  They are the following:"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "eq. of Alexander-Gazdik, Phys.Rev,120(1960)874, and",
                "Phys.Rev,129(1963)259, given as",
                "   R = K * (E **(3/2)), R=range and E=kinetic energy,",
                "and K is a constant which varies slowly with the mass."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "eq. of Prakash, thesis, Univ.of Bombay,1971, given as",
                "   R = C * ((square root(E))*(square root(A1))/((F)*",
                "   ((Z1)**(1/3)))",
                "where the range R of a fission product of mass number",
                "A1 with the most probable charge Z1 and energy E are",
                "related with (F).  (F) includes the light and heavy",
                "primary mass numbers and their most probable charges,",
                "density of the stopping medium and the electronic",
                "charge.  (C) is a constant.   See text for detail."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MISC-COL": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MISC1"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Recoil range, in milli-gram/cm2."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MISC2"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 'Primary' mass of light fission fragment.",
                "Accordingly, mass of heavy fragment(primary) is to be,",
                "  (237+1) - (primary mass of light fission fragment).",
                "The 'primary' mass was obtained by adding to the mass",
                "of the measured fission product the average number of",
                "neutrons per fission emitted by this fragment,using",
                "the neutron emission curve for Pu-239 of Apalin et al.",
                "Nucl. Phys. 71,553 (1965)."
              ]
            }
          ],
